### Initializing Retrieval Object in TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/ragieai/ragie-typescript/blob/main/docs/models/components/retrieval.md

This snippet demonstrates how to initialize a `Retrieval` object in TypeScript, showcasing its expected structure. It includes an array of `scoredChunks`, each containing text, a relevance score, unique identifiers, and detailed document metadata and links. This structure is crucial for representing retrieved information in a standardized format.

```typescript
import { Retrieval } from "ragie/models/components";

let value: Retrieval = {
  scoredChunks: [
    {
      text: "<value>",
      score: 2691.35,
      id: "<id>",
      index: 522812,
      documentId: "<id>",
      documentName: "<value>",
      documentMetadata: {
        "key": "<value>"
      },
      links: {
        "key": {
          href: "<value>",
          type: "<value>"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
};
```

