### Performing Retrieval with Standalone Function in TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/ragieai/ragie-typescript/blob/main/docs/sdks/retrievals/README.md

This example illustrates using the standalone `retrievalsRetrieve` function for better tree-shaking performance. It initializes `RagieCore` once and then calls the function, passing the core instance and retrieval parameters. It includes error handling to check if the response is successful before accessing the result.

```typescript
import { RagieCore } from "ragie/core.js";
import { retrievalsRetrieve } from "ragie/funcs/retrievalsRetrieve.js";

// Use `RagieCore` for best tree-shaking performance.
// You can create one instance of it to use across an application.
const ragie = new RagieCore({
  auth: "<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>",
});

async function run() {
  const res = await retrievalsRetrieve(ragie, {
    query: "What is the best pizza place in SF?",
    maxChunksPerDocument: 0,
    partition: "<value>",
  });

  if (!res.ok) {
    throw res.error;
  }

  const { value: result } = res;

  // Handle the result
  console.log(result);
}

run();
```

